Package fi.abo.kogni.soile2.projecthandling.apielements

Interface APIElement<T extends ElementBase>

All Known Implementing Classes:
APIElementBase, APIExperiment, APIProject, APITask
public interface APIElement<T extends ElementBase>
Objects that implement this class reflect elements in a database that allow linking to a gitRepository. They also store all Versions
Author:
Thomas Pfau

    • getDBElement

      io.vertx.core.Future<T> getDBElement(io.vertx.ext.mongo.MongoClient client, ElementFactory<T> elementFactory)
      Get a Future of an (updated) element from the database. Note, this element will Be updated with the information provided in the API Element and can directly be saved in order to update the database object.
      Parameters:
      client - the mongoclient to use to save the data
      elementFactory - the elementFactory used to build the element

    • hasAdditionalGitContent

      boolean hasAdditionalGitContent()
      Test whether this API Element has additional Content stored in the git repository besides the pure object data. If true, the additional data will be stored using storeAdditonalGitData and loaded via its loadAdditionalGitData functions
      Returns:
      this API Element has additional Content stored in the git repository

    • storeAdditionalData

      io.vertx.core.Future<String> storeAdditionalData(String currentVersion, io.vertx.core.eventbus.EventBus eb, String targetRepository)
      Store additional data to the git Manager, returns a future of the new git repo version with the data stored.
      Parameters:
      currentVersion - the version on which to base the additions
      eb - EventBus used for to contact git
      targetRepository - name of the target repository
      Returns:
      A Future of the updated version
